set_socv_rc_variation_factor(25.10)        set_socv_rc_variation_factor(25.10)

Name
       set_socv_rc_variation_factor  - Defines the value of interconnect delay
       variation factor

Syntax
       set_socv_rc_variation_factor

       [-help]

       <variation_factor>

       [-early]

       [-late]

       [-view <list_of_views>]

       Defines the value of interconnect delay variation factor.

       This command applies global variation as percentage of the nominal  de-
       lay.

       To  enable  this feature, you can set the timing_socv_rc_variation_mode
       global variable to true.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage

       <variation_factor>
              Specifies the value of the interconnect delay  variation  factor
              to be used.

       -early Specifies the variation factor for early interconnect delays.

       -late  Specifies the variation factor for late interconnect delays.

       -view <list_of_views>
              Apply  the  SOCV  interconnect variation factor to the specified
              list of analysis views.

